From a1d19a0e3b51ca374df9b6137243251cf939e5bd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Sun, 22 Mar 2026 12:31:33 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 036/174] PGCL: alpha boot, mips TLB fixes, debug print
 cleanup, arm32 regression fix
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Alpha PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4 boot support (8 files):
- pgtable.h: PMD_SHIFT/PGDIR_SHIFT use MMUPAGE_SHIFT, pfn_pte/pte_pfn
  handle hardware PFN ↔ kernel PFN conversion, add __phys_to_pte_val
- mmu_context.h: pgd physical address uses MMUPAGE_SHIFT
- entry.S/head.S: kernel page table setup uses MMUPAGE_SHIFT for
  hardware PTE entries
- osf_sys.c: mmap offset alignment uses MMUPAGE_SHIFT
- setup.c/init.c/fault.c: MMUPAGE fixes for memory init and fault handling

MIPS TLB exception handler fixes (tlbex.c, 7 locations):
- Software TLB refill code uses hardware page size (MMUPAGE_SHIFT)
  not kernel page size for PTE index calculation and page walk
- PTRS_PER_PTE → MMUPAGE_SIZE/sizeof(pte_t) for hardware PTE count
- HTW (Hardware Table Walker) page walk fields use MMUPAGE_SHIFT

ARM32 regression fix (mmu.c):
- Removing debug pr_alert left orphan 'if (addr >= 0xffff0000)' that
  guarded the entire do-while PTE fill loop — all mappings below
  0xffff0000 got zero PTEs, crashing in atomic_pool_init

Debug print removal (11 files, ~95 prints):
- Remove PGCL diagnostic prints from arm32, init/main.c, binfmt_elf.c,
  workqueue.c, arch_topology.c, fdt.c, page_alloc.c, pgtable.h

Alpha boots with 15/15 pgcl-test + 8/8 pgcl-stress PASS.
8 architectures now boot with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
